<Base>
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="bg-blue-100 py-20 px-4">
        <div class="container mx-auto text-center">
            <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-6xl font-extrabold leading-tight mb-10 animate-fade-in-up">
                Learn to craft your own perfect productivity system
            </h1>
            <div class="text-center"> <!-- Centering the single button -->
                <a data-formkit-toggle="f311597e4f" href="https://creadevlabs.kit.com/f311597e4f" class="bg-orange-300 text-white px-8 py-4 rounded-full shadow-lg hover:bg-orange-400 transition duration-300 ease-in-out text-lg font-bold">
                  Subscribe to My Newsletter
                </a>
            </div>
        </div>
  </section>

    <!-- Problem Statement Section -->
    <section class="py-16 px-4">
        <div class="container mx-auto text-center">
            <p class="text-xl text-gray-700 max-w-4xl mx-auto mb-12">
                You've invested time and effort into every popular task manager and expert's framework, only to find them rigid, incomplete, or simply not aligned with how <em class="font-semibold">you</em> work.
            </p>
            <p class="text-xl text-gray-700 max-w-4xl mx-auto">
                Why is it that everyone else seems to have it all figured out, but you always fall short?
            </p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Your Unique Path to Productivity Section -->
    <section class="py-16 px-4 bg-gray-50">
        <div class="container mx-auto text-center">
            <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8 text-gray-900">Your Unique Path to Productivity</h2>
            <p class="text-xl text-gray-700 max-w-4xl mx-auto mb-12">
                The reason those "perfect" systems never quite work for you is simple: <strong class="font-semibold">productivity is deeply personal.</strong> You'll never achieve your full potential by adopting someone else's personalized framework. They built their system for themselves, not for you.
            </p>
            <p class="text-xl text-gray-700 max-w-4xl mx-auto">
                My approach isn't about teaching you <em class="font-semibold">my</em> specific system; it's about guiding you through a simple process to <strong class="font-semibold">craft a perfectly tailored productivity system designed to meet your needs.</strong>
            </p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Learn the Framework, Master the Tools Section -->
    <section class="py-16 px-4 bg-white">
        <div class="container mx-auto">
            <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold text-center mb-12 text-gray-900">Learn the Framework, Master the Tools</h2>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-10">
                <!-- Column 1: The FIRST Framework -->
                <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-xl shadow-lg hover:shadow-2xl transition duration-300 ease-in-out transform border border-gray-200">
                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-center mb-4 text-gray-900">The FIRST Framework</h3>
                    <div class="text-blue-600 mb-4 text-center">
                        <Image src={firstOverview} width="200" alt="FIRST Framework Overview" />
                    </div>
                    <p class="text-gray-700 text-center mb-4">
                        Where do you start when crafting your perfect productivity system? Start with FIRST! It's a simple framework I've developed to help you craft the perfect system to meet your specific needs.
                    </p>
                    <p class="mt-4 text-center">
                        <a href="#" class="inline-block bg-blue-600 text-white text-sm font-semibold px-4 py-2 rounded-full hover:bg-blue-700 transition duration-300">Learn More</a>
                    </p>
                </div>
                <!-- Column 2: Obsidian as a Flexible Tool -->
                <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-xl shadow-lg hover:shadow-2xl transition duration-300 ease-in-out transform border border-gray-200">
                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-center mb-4 text-gray-900">Master Obsidian</h3>
                    <div class="text-blue-600 mb-4 text-center">
                        <Image src={obsidianLogo} width="200" alt="Obsidian Logo" />
                    </div>
                    <p class="text-gray-700 text-center mb-4">
                        While FIRST works with any app, I recommend learning and using Obsidian. It's a highly flexible tool for building a personalized productivity system. Its adaptability allows you to shape it precisely to your needs, unlike rigid, off-the-shelf solutions.
                    </p>
                    <p class="mt-4 text-center">
                        <a href="https://youtube.com/@creadevlabs" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="inline-block bg-red-600 text-white text-sm font-semibold px-4 py-2 rounded-full hover:bg-red-700 transition duration-300">Learn Obsidian on YouTube</a>
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Need a Little More Help? Section -->
    <section class="py-16 px-4 bg-gray-50">
        <div class="container mx-auto">
            <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold text-center mb-12 text-gray-900">Need a Little More Help?</h2>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-10">
                <!-- Service 1: Productivity Pals -->
                <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-xl shadow-lg hover:shadow-2xl transition duration-300 ease-in-out transform border border-gray-200">
                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-center mb-4 text-gray-900">Productivity Pals</h3>
                    <div class="text-blue-600 mb-4 text-center">
                        <Image src={productivityPalsLogo} width="200" alt="Productivity Pals Logo" />
                    </div>
                    <p class="text-gray-700 text-center">
                        You don't have to journey towards perfect productivity alone! Join Productivity Pals, a small, yet growing community dedicated to building and perfecting personalized productivity systems. Connect with like-minded individuals, share real-world insights, and actively hone your personalized productivity system alongside supportive peers.
                    </p>
                    <p class="mt-4 text-center">
                        <a href="https://productivitypals.creadevlabs.com" class="inline-block bg-green-600 text-white text-sm font-semibold px-4 py-2 rounded-full hover:bg-green-700 transition duration-300">Join Today!</a>
                    </p>
                </div>
                <!-- Service 2: Gamified Task Manager -->
                <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-xl shadow-lg hover:shadow-2xl transition duration-300 ease-in-out transform border border-gray-200">
                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-center mb-4 text-gray-900">Gamified Task Manager</h3>
                    <div class="text-blue-600 mb-4 text-center">
                        <Image src={gamifiedTaskManagerLogo} width="200" alt="Gamified Task Manager Logo" />
                    </div>
                    <p class="text-gray-700 text-center">
                        Building your own system sounds great in theory, but sometimes you need something ready to go out of the box. That system still needs to be flexible, and should also have an element of fun. That's why I've been developing a gamified task manager that combines a real world task manager with a cozy video game! It'll feature a customizable task manager where completing your real life tasks will give you rewards to use in a fantasy adventure. You can follow the development of the project over on YouTube!
                    </p>
                    <p class="mt-4 text-center">
                        <a href="https://youtube.com/playlist?list=PLsntwn2ixQrM6njdiIoIgbA8HgqJqtE0N&si=DHi2Uy1gYYhXyCMv" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="inline-block bg-red-600 text-white text-sm font-semibold px-4 py-2 rounded-full hover:bg-red-700 transition duration-300">Follow on YouTube</a>
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

